=> WHAT IS JS ?
    JS STANDS JAVASCRIPT WHICH IS USED TO PERFORM OPERATIONS ON A WEBPAGE.
    USE TO SEND OR RECEIVE DATA FROM SERVERS.

    JAVASCRIPT IS A SCRIPTING LANGUAGE WHICH IS LIGHT WEIGHT. 

=> IN HOW MANY WAYS WE CAN USE JS ?
    THERE ARE THREE WAYS TO USE JS 
        1. inside of body tag
        2. inside of head tag   
        3. external js 

=> TO LINK EXTERNAL JS WHICH TAG AND ATTRIBUTE DO WE USE ?
    script tag is used to link external js 
    and 'src' attribute is used to link particular file 

